Solution 1:

`default_nettype none
module top_module(
    input a,
    input b,
    input c,
    input d,
    output out,
    output out_n   ); 
	
    wire tmp_1, tmp_2;
    assign tmp_1 = a& b;
    assign tmp_2 = c& d;
    assign out = tmp_1| tmp_2;
    assign out_n = ~out;
    
endmodule

Solution 2: 
NOTE:	this will not be correct according to the requirements of the problem.  
	But instead of declaring wire, how to realize the same function?
	By stuffing the entire logic. 

`default_nettype none
module top_module(
    input a,
    input b,
    input c,
    input d,
    output out,
    output out_n   ); 
	
    assign out = (a&b)| (c&d);
    assign out_n = ~out;
    
endmodule
